$ DOM example: offsetWidth / offsetHeight

An *element's* `offsetWidth` and `offsetHeight` evaluate to the width and height that an element actually occupies. Included in these dimensions is
  • border
  • padding
  • vertical scrollbar (if shown)
Not included is the element's margin.

gh|about-Document-Object-Model|/Node/Element/offsetWidth-offsetHeight.html||

On my computer, this test wrote the following text into the console window:
code {
txt.offsetWidth  = 77
txt.offsetHeight = 17
stl.width        = auto
stl.height       = auto
code }

